HB 299 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Melerine
Abstract: Provides for the filing of a jury bond in person, by U.S. mail, or commercial
courier.
Present law provides for the filing of documents in court in person or by electronic form.
Further provides that certain documents may be filed in person, by U.S. mail, or commercial
courier.
Proposed law retains present law and extends the permissible filing by person, by U.S. mail,
or commercial courier to jury bonds.
(Amends C.C.P Art. 253(B)(3)(intro. para.); Adds C.C.P. Art. 253(B)(3)(e))
